# TypeScript

- Strict mode is on (`tsconfig.base.json`). Do not weaken `strict`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, or related flags.
- Prefer `unknown` over `any`. Avoid new `any` and `@ts-expect-error` without a one-line reason.
- Shared request/response shapes live in `@nova/shared` (Zod schemas). Rebuild `@nova/shared` after schema edits so `dist` types stay current.
- API imports use `@/` path aliases; do not introduce conflicting path maps.
- Prefer explicit return types on exported public functions in `lib/` when inference is ambiguous.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — consumer still sees old types
// edit packages/shared/src/types/api.ts and skip build

// ✅ GOOD
// edit schema, then:
// pnpm --filter @nova/shared build
```
